---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Sergio Y. Lee">
  <h1 class="font-serif text-foreground mb-1">Sergio Y. Lee</h1>
  <p class="font-mono text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-10">
    Software Engineer &mdash; Systems, Compilers, Performance
  </p>

  <p>
    I write software for a living. I've been doing this for over a decade, mostly in the layers
    of the stack that most people prefer to ignore: runtimes, compilers, operating systems, and
    anything that runs close to the metal.
  </p>

  <p>
    I care about correctness first, then speed. I don't use frameworks unless they solve a
    problem I actually have. I ship things that work.
  </p>

  <p>
    This site is a record of what I've built, what I've learned, and where I stand. No
    buzzwords, no brand.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2 class="font-serif mb-4">Recent work</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="/work#raft">Distributed key-value store with Raft consensus</a>
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-muted-foreground ml-2">2024</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/work#jit">JIT compiler for a custom bytecode VM</a>
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-muted-foreground ml-2">2023</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/work#allocator">Custom memory allocator replacing system malloc</a>
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-muted-foreground ml-2">2023</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/work#profiler">Sampling profiler for Linux user-space processes</a>
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-muted-foreground ml-2">2022</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>
